New Records: Serhou Guirassy scored the first hat-trick in 2025 qualifying and made him the joint leading scorer with Algerian Amine Gouiri, Egyptian Mahmoud 'Trezeguet' Hassan and Ivorian Jean-Philippe Krasso
Key Match Events: Azzedine Ounahi netted twice and Abde Ezzalzouli, Achraf Hakimi and Soufiane Rahimi once each as Morocco eased to victory in Oujda
Pre-Game Insights: It was a predictable Group B outcome as 114 places separate top-ranked African team Morocco from the Central African Republic
Post-Match Reflections: Morocco qualify automatically for the AFCON as hosts, with the tournament due to start on December 21, 2025 and finish on January 18, 2026
Miscellaneous Highlights: DR Congo top the table with nine points, and share perfect records halfway through qualifying with Algeria, Angola, Egypt, Ivory Coast and Morocco
